<p class="title"><span class="title-box">1st Stage ‹NieR Gestalt & RepliCant›</span></p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil's Words</span></p>
<p class="para">In the distant past, our world was on the brink of destruction.
<br>A deadly illness ran rampant, decimating the population.``
<br>And on the edges of towns, the number of terrifying monsters known as ‘Shades’ continued to rise.
<br>This story begins in a small village.
A young man’s little sister is infected with the illness, and he desperately struggles to save her.
<br><br>
A young man… with a very kind heart.
<br><br>
As time passes, memories scatter like sand in the wind.
<br>I might forget everything someday.
<br>But my memories of that journey are my most precious treasures.
<br><br>
We fought together.
<br>We laughed together.
<br>We cried together.
<br>They were kind, caring friends.
<br><br>
We came to know many truths on our journey.
<br>The truth of a society bound by rules.
<br>The truth of broken machines and people.
<br>And the truth that the Shades we thought were monsters had minds of their own.
<br><br>
Hey Kainé…?
<br>Were we right to do what we did?
<br><br>
At long last, we arrived at our final destination: the Shadowlord’s castle.
<br>There we learned the human race had already gone extinct—
<br>and we witnessed the solitude of those who safeguarded that truth.
<br><br>
At the end of our journey, all we found was a hollow, meaningless future.
<br><br>
Kainé, you’ve been gone for a really long time.
<br>My memories of those days are falling apart;
<br>I don’t remember much anymore.
<br><br>
But I… I miss everyone.
<br>I miss everyone so much...</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Concert Part.1</span></p>
<p class="para">(While most of the songs were performed, short text stories were shown on the screen)</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">What I wanted to protect...and what I lost. (Snow in Summer)</span></p>
<p class="para">Cold show swirling on a summer’s day. The world was ending.
<br>In a town with no food to sate you or places to keep you safe.
<br>Nary a soul willing to save a pair of orphaned siblings.
<br>All I can do for my little sister is hold her small, cold hand.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A predetermined fate, and a miscalculation. (Song of the Ancients)</span></p>
<p class="para">Long ago, there were two siblings who were the best of friends.
<br>The little sister came down with an incurable illness.
<br>The illness was called the Black Scrawl.
<br>The older brother swore to save his sister at any cost.
<br>At any cost.</p>
