<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2nd Stage ‹NieR:Automata›</span></p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B's Words</span></p>
<p class="para">We YoRHa were created to annihilate our enemies, the machine lifeforms.
<br>Yet what we encountered upon landing on Earth were machines that ignored their own nature as weapons and made no attempt to fight.
<br>9S and I made contact, trying all the while to figure out what was happening…
<br><br>
My mission with 9S was rigorous, but occasionally enjoyable.
<br><br>
The warm sun filtering into the ruins…
<br>The laughter of Pascal and the children…
<br>The whistling of the wind through the forest…
<br>Taking breaks at the Resistance Camp…
<br>Seeing the light of a beautiful ocean…
<br><br>
I wanted to remember those moments forever…
<br><br>
As I stifled the unease deep in my heart.
<br>Amidst that ceaseless killing, I realized something.
<br><br>
The aliens met their end at the hands of the machine lifeforms.
<br>Our beloved Council of Humanity was a lie.
<br>The machine lifeforms suffered… as they search for a reason to exist.
<br><br>
We were at a loss… as we pondered who we ought to fight for.
<br><br>
It was as if…we were praying to gods.
<br><br>
After everything was destroyed, I realized something. YoRHa was…
<br><br>
No, not just YoRHa. All things –including ourselves– were born for a reason.
<br>Even if our world is cursed and drowning in despair.
<br>Even then… I have a mission I must complete.
<br>That is why I met you.
<br><br>
Be it in the solitude after my birth, or in the darkness before my death,
you were always by my side… Weren’t you?
<br><br>
Thank you, Nines.</p>
